おもしろそうに　およいでる
by themonk » Tue 09.06.2011 4:46 pm Sensei:I understand the part for ''interesting" and "swimming," but not the ending part in bold.I suspect that they are grammar related. Any idea? おもしろそうに　およいでるThis line is from the Koi song.
themonk
Posts: 78Joined: Mon 09.20.2010 8:31 am
Native language: NA
Top
Re: おもしろそうに　およいでる
by Hyperworm » Tue 09.06.2011 5:36 pm These two forms are1. the そう form of 面白い turned into an adverb with に (overall meaning and why そう is used)2. the te-form of 泳ぐ, + いる (てる/でる is a casual contraction of ている/でいる)
fun translation snippets | need something translated?BTC@1KMZXgoWiDshQis5Z7feCx8jaiP4QAB2ks
